In our model for n-type Si (default by the employed software), τmin is 0 s, τmax is 2.08 × 10−6 s, γ is 1, and Nref is 3 × 10−6 cm−3. The surface recombination is approximated to be a SRH process, which is present through deep defect levels in the gap. The surface recombination velocity (SRV) in unit of cm−2 s−1 in this model can be obtained from the τsur via following equation:2SRV=tsurτsur\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
